Rating, 4 stars,  · November 2023,  · Stayed over a week
rating_comment: The Owner did not show photos of the Unit. Not transparent with the furnishings. I needed a desk in the room (I did not know I could request one! I Was granted a table and 2 chairs 5 days before checkout! - thankfully).

It was my second time staying at Maati and it was a wonderful experience once again. The service was phenomenal and the living condition, I'd say has improved even further. Overall, it was a delight staying here and will definitely look forward to booking my accommodations right here on my next and future visits.

info: Rating, 5 stars,  · March 2023,  · Stayed about a week
rating_comment:
Stayed here for nine nights.
First visit to Bangladesh. Very friendly and helpful people.
The apartment block is close to many amenities.
The Jumana Future Park is a short walk away. Supermarket is in the basement. Lots of shops and restaurants in the complex.
The Crimson Cup coffee shop nearby is great for breakfast or lunch.
Swimming pool on roof is great value. 200 taka for the week. I had the pool to myself every time au used it.
All staff friendly and helpful.
Wi-Fi good in room.
Use Uber to get around. Very reliable.
Super stay. Highly recommended for the price paid *****
